        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation relevance acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, the same blood analogue fluid, and operating conditions spanning the COU envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM)."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry using the AAMI PD 55 blood analogue (glycerol-water mixture). All five COU operating points were included in the validation matrix. Geometric fidelity confirmed by CMM measurement of test hardware."
